00:15:49.762 --> 00:15:51.055
What empowers us

00:15:51.138 --> 00:15:55.142
is jealousy, envy, and fear,
not love from the people.

00:15:55.225 --> 00:15:58.145
But you're making it easier

00:15:58.228 --> 00:16:01.732
for people to bring up
our firm so casually

00:16:02.399 --> 00:16:04.401
by gathering low-class losers

00:16:05.194 --> 00:16:07.821
to represent a dog, a kid with disability,

00:16:07.905 --> 00:16:10.741
and an illegal alien.

00:16:12.117 --> 00:16:14.495
I thought I'd taught you enough
about how power works.

00:16:15.162 --> 00:16:17.122
Are you dumb?

00:16:17.790 --> 00:16:20.751
Or have you become weak
like your dead mother?

00:16:25.506 --> 00:16:27.257
I'll prove it with numbers.

00:16:29.176 --> 00:16:31.178
-What?
-I just need to show you

00:16:31.261 --> 00:16:33.097
that we can be profitable, right?

00:16:33.180 --> 00:16:34.264
How about this?

00:16:34.348 --> 00:16:37.768
Baekseung Law Firm has been
close behind Oh & Partners in revenue.

00:16:37.851 --> 00:16:40.479
What if we can take away their clients?

00:16:41.980 --> 00:16:43.065
Mr. Kang.

00:16:43.148 --> 00:16:44.733
Hey, Judge Kang.

00:16:44.817 --> 00:16:47.402
I like to gamble too,

00:16:47.486 --> 00:16:52.157
but one needs something at stake
to make a bet work.

00:16:52.241 --> 00:16:54.159
I've already ordered the disbandment.

00:16:57.371 --> 00:16:58.747
If we lose,

00:17:00.582 --> 00:17:03.127
we'll disband the team for free.

00:17:03.210 --> 00:17:04.419
For free?

00:17:04.503 --> 00:17:06.380
If you force us to disband,

00:17:06.463 --> 00:17:09.550
I'll immediately sue you
for wrongful termination.

00:17:09.633 --> 00:17:13.428
And of course,
I'll drag it out as much as possible

00:17:13.512 --> 00:17:14.805
until your costs pile up.

00:17:16.807 --> 00:17:17.808
How interesting.

00:17:25.983 --> 00:17:27.901
Please let me know. I'll wait.

00:17:32.114 --> 00:17:33.115
Also,

00:17:33.824 --> 00:17:35.576
let me correct one thing.

00:17:36.326 --> 00:17:38.745
The person we represented, Kaya,
wasn't an illegal alien.

00:17:39.413 --> 00:17:43.125
She came to Korea legitimately
with a marriage visa.

00:17:43.208 --> 00:17:48.547
I was taught that fact-checking
is a basic requirement for any attorney.

00:17:56.138 --> 00:17:56.972
A bet?

00:17:59.725 --> 00:18:00.726
Sounds good.

00:18:07.065 --> 00:18:08.942
Thank you, Mr. Jang.

00:18:09.026 --> 00:18:10.903
Don't worry. You trust me, right?

00:18:11.528 --> 00:18:12.362
Yes.

00:18:15.073 --> 00:18:16.742
-Goodbye.
-Take care.

00:18:19.328 --> 00:18:21.747
-By the way, Mr. Jang.
-Yes?

00:18:22.414 --> 00:18:24.708
You're so handsome.

00:18:29.004 --> 00:18:29.922
What?

00:18:33.383 --> 00:18:34.760
Hey, handsome lawyer man.

00:18:35.844 --> 00:18:37.554
Why are you blushing?

00:18:37.638 --> 00:18:39.181
Well, I'm not ugly.

00:18:40.057 --> 00:18:41.433
-My goodness.
-Yeong-sil.

00:18:43.435 --> 00:18:45.020
She's Song Ji-hye, isn't she?

00:18:45.103 --> 00:18:46.939
I heard a social worker sent her to you.

00:18:47.022 --> 00:18:50.150
Yes. Ji-hye has
a Grade 3 intellectual disability,

00:18:50.234 --> 00:18:52.736
and her parents passed away
from a car accident.

00:18:52.819 --> 00:18:53.987
Goodness.

00:18:54.071 --> 00:18:55.113
Really?

00:18:58.325 --> 00:18:59.493
Gather around.

00:19:00.118 --> 00:19:01.578
I have something to tell you.

00:19:03.664 --> 00:19:04.957
A competition?

00:19:05.040 --> 00:19:09.127
We're pro bono attorneys.
We're people who defend the weak.

00:19:09.211 --> 00:19:11.713
Baekseung only handles cases
with tax-evading chaebols

00:19:11.797 --> 00:19:13.715
and corporate raiders
who conduct mass layoffs.

00:19:13.799 --> 00:19:15.342
You want us to take that kind of case?

00:19:15.425 --> 00:19:18.387
Do you know who Mr. Jang
just agreed to represent?

00:19:18.470 --> 00:19:20.180
An abused intellectually disabled person.

00:19:20.264 --> 00:19:23.267
We're attorneys
who help those kinds of people.

00:19:26.228 --> 00:19:30.315
We're the ones getting laid off here.
We're the weak.

00:19:30.399 --> 00:19:33.193
Can't you think of it
as defending ourselves?

00:19:33.277 --> 00:19:36.530
But you should've made a bet we could win.

00:19:36.613 --> 00:19:38.073
If we lose this epically,

00:19:38.156 --> 00:19:40.409
someone like me
won't be able to find another job.

00:19:40.492 --> 00:19:42.244
We'll just win then!

00:19:49.084 --> 00:19:51.420
Yes, this is Team Pro Bono. Sorry?

00:19:53.088 --> 00:19:54.047
Yes.

00:19:56.174 --> 00:20:00.470
Mr. Bae wants all of us
to come to the conference room at once.

00:20:00.554 --> 00:20:01.638
Right now?

00:20:03.473 --> 00:20:05.392
It's almost time,
so take care of it quickly.

00:20:10.522 --> 00:20:11.606
-Hello.
-Hello, sir!

00:20:11.690 --> 00:20:12.524
Hello.

00:20:13.233 --> 00:20:15.277
Why did you need us so urgently?

00:20:15.360 --> 00:20:18.905
Attorney Kang, I heard you made
an "adorable" proposal to Dr. Oh.

00:20:19.614 --> 00:20:21.992
You promised to beat Baekseung
to secure a case?

00:20:24.494 --> 00:20:27.414
Yes, "whatever" case that maybe.

00:20:27.497 --> 00:20:31.001
Really? "Any" case, right?

00:20:33.795 --> 00:20:35.172
How may I help you?

00:20:35.255 --> 00:20:37.424
We have an appointment
with Oh & Partners at noon.

00:20:39.885 --> 00:20:40.886
You mean her?

00:20:55.025 --> 00:20:58.278
We happen to have a meeting today,
so give it your best.

00:20:58.362 --> 00:21:00.572
They're coming here
after meeting with Baekseung.

00:21:00.655 --> 00:21:03.492
You suddenly called us here
to meet with a client?

00:21:03.575 --> 00:21:05.535
What? The first meeting's
only for introductions.

00:21:06.953 --> 00:21:10.040
You made a bet with Dr. Oh
without even having that much confidence?

00:21:10.665 --> 00:21:13.794
Keep your word and disband the team
without any complaints if you lose.

00:21:15.212 --> 00:21:16.671
They should be here by now.

00:21:16.755 --> 00:21:18.632
-Why are you standing like that? Sit.
-Right.

00:21:18.715 --> 00:21:19.800
Behave yourselves.

00:21:19.883 --> 00:21:22.052
Don't make a scene or scream.

00:21:22.135 --> 00:21:23.720
Scream?

00:21:24.346 --> 00:21:25.430
Hello.

00:21:25.514 --> 00:21:26.473
It's Elijah.

00:21:30.143 --> 00:21:34.106
Oh, my gosh! It's Elijah! I'm a big fan!

00:21:34.189 --> 00:21:35.774
Elijah!

00:21:35.857 --> 00:21:38.985
-What's going on?
-Sir, Elijah is here.

00:21:39.528 --> 00:21:40.654
-Elijah?
-Yes!

00:21:40.737 --> 00:21:41.905
-"Korea's sweetheart"?
-Yes!

00:21:41.988 --> 00:21:43.407
Let's go take a photo!

00:21:44.533 --> 00:21:45.951
They must be here.

00:21:46.618 --> 00:21:48.036
Goodness, welcome.

00:21:48.662 --> 00:21:49.913
Hello.

00:21:51.498 --> 00:21:52.582
No way.

00:21:54.918 --> 00:21:57.379
It's Elijah. What is she doing here?

00:21:59.047 --> 00:21:59.923
I'm sorry.

00:22:00.006 --> 00:22:03.552
Mr. Hwang's a big fan,
so he must've gotten excited for a moment.

00:22:04.261 --> 00:22:06.054
-I'm not late, am I?
-No, it's all right.

00:22:06.763 --> 00:22:10.142
Hello, I'm Attorney Bae Yong-hun
of Oh & Partners.

00:22:10.225 --> 00:22:11.059
Nice to meet you.

00:22:11.143 --> 00:22:12.769
-I'm Cha Jin-hui.
-Hello, sir.

00:22:13.979 --> 00:22:16.314
By the way, who are these people?

00:22:16.398 --> 00:22:18.108
-Right.
-Hello.

00:22:18.191 --> 00:22:22.404
I'm Attorney Kang Da-wit,
former chief judge

00:22:22.487 --> 00:22:25.240
of Seoul Central District Court.

00:22:25.323 --> 00:22:26.241
I see.

00:22:26.324 --> 00:22:28.201
Hello, I'm Park Gi-ppeum.

00:22:28.285 --> 00:22:29.244
Okay.

00:22:29.327 --> 00:22:31.329
I'm Hwang Jun-u. I'm a big fan.

00:22:31.413 --> 00:22:34.624
I'm Jang Yeong-sil.

00:22:35.750 --> 00:22:38.795
Geez. Why do I smell oil?

00:22:39.421 --> 00:22:41.673
I'm sorry. I was in the middle of work
before I came.

00:22:42.257 --> 00:22:46.970
-I'm sorry.
-The vibe of Oh & Partners' attorneys is…

00:22:48.305 --> 00:22:49.848
very colorful.

00:22:50.640 --> 00:22:53.685
Everyone at Baekseung Law Firm
went to SNU Law School.

00:22:53.768 --> 00:22:56.438
Their team leader is
a former CID prosecutor from the SPO.

00:22:56.521 --> 00:22:58.690
The SPO's
Central Investigation Department?

00:23:00.066 --> 00:23:01.067
Mr. Woo Myeong-hun?

00:23:01.151 --> 00:23:02.277
Yes.

00:23:02.360 --> 00:23:06.114
I assume you obviously went to SNU
if you're a former chief judge?

00:23:11.870 --> 00:23:13.079
Am I wrong?

00:23:14.998 --> 00:23:19.419
I specifically asked for a team
with the best attorneys.

00:23:19.502 --> 00:23:22.380
Ms. Cha, this team's been
on a roll these days.

00:23:22.964 --> 00:23:25.425
You must've seen them on the news.
Team Pro Bono.

00:23:26.968 --> 00:23:27.802
Team Pro Bono?

00:23:28.678 --> 00:23:30.972
From that abandoned dog case?

00:23:31.056 --> 00:23:33.016
-That…
-Yes!

00:23:33.099 --> 00:23:36.186
Yes, we handled that case.

00:23:36.853 --> 00:23:40.732
Wait, did you bring me a team
that handles dog cases?

00:23:41.566 --> 00:23:42.943
I knew it.

00:23:43.026 --> 00:23:45.654
You can't bring in nobodies like this.

00:23:47.155 --> 00:23:48.740
"Nobodies"?

00:23:48.823 --> 00:23:52.410
We're not the people
who can be called nobodies.

00:23:52.494 --> 00:23:54.496
I'm sure you have heard about me.

00:23:54.579 --> 00:23:55.872
The people's judge--

00:23:56.873 --> 00:23:57.916
What?

00:23:59.417 --> 00:24:03.922
You can't just give yourself
such a title like that.

00:24:04.005 --> 00:24:08.009
I didn't give myself the title.
Then, let me explain in detail.

00:24:08.093 --> 00:24:10.845
The number of my followers is--

00:24:13.098 --> 00:24:14.140
I'm sorry.

00:24:14.224 --> 00:24:17.394
Our team leader's had to pull
a lot of all-nighters these days.

00:24:17.477 --> 00:24:18.478
-You must be tired.
-No.

00:24:18.561 --> 00:24:21.147
Shall we begin the meeting
after a short break?

00:24:21.231 --> 00:24:22.899
-We just met.
-Okay, come here.

00:24:22.983 --> 00:24:25.652
Elijah, I'm a big fan. It's such an honor.

00:24:25.735 --> 00:24:27.654
-Ms. Park, why…
-Come here.

00:24:27.737 --> 00:24:29.447
-Wait, that's not…
-You're so heavy.

00:24:29.531 --> 00:24:31.199
Ms. Park, what I meant was…

00:24:31.283 --> 00:24:32.367
Let go of me.

00:24:32.993 --> 00:24:34.536
Will you hear me out?

00:24:34.619 --> 00:24:36.579
She keeps saying
Seoul National University.

00:24:36.663 --> 00:24:39.040
What, did she graduate
from an elite school

00:24:39.124 --> 00:24:40.959
to become a celebrity?

00:24:41.042 --> 00:24:43.086
-Elijah goes to a prestigious university.
-Yes.

00:24:44.129 --> 00:24:45.213
-Really?
-Yes.

00:24:46.423 --> 00:24:48.758
How many followers does she have then?

00:24:48.842 --> 00:24:51.052
Ms. Park, I have 380,000 followers now.

00:24:51.886 --> 00:24:54.848
She has 25 million.

00:24:57.851 --> 00:24:59.811
25 MILLION FOLLOWERS

00:24:59.894 --> 00:25:03.773
Mr. Kang, who was
the last K-pop idol you liked?

00:25:10.447 --> 00:25:12.741
-Tell me--
-Mr. Kang!

00:25:12.824 --> 00:25:15.243
How can you not know Elijah,
"Korea's sweetheart"

00:25:15.327 --> 00:25:17.579
and the one everyone wishes
was their daughter?

00:25:17.662 --> 00:25:20.165
An angel with a beautiful smile
who donates to charities,

00:25:20.248 --> 00:25:22.792
she got into a top college
while working hard as an idol.

00:25:22.876 --> 00:25:24.794
Elijah is every parent's dream!

00:25:25.712 --> 00:25:27.589
Why are you so quiet? This isn't like you.

00:25:27.672 --> 00:25:29.174
Don't you know who Elijah is?

00:25:29.257 --> 00:25:30.633
-Am I supposed to know?
-Well?

00:25:31.259 --> 00:25:34.262
Anyway, her group was disbanded
three years ago,

00:25:34.346 --> 00:25:36.639
and she debuted
as a solo artist last year.

00:25:36.723 --> 00:25:38.767
EK Entertainment CEO Cha Jin-hui
is her mother.

00:25:38.850 --> 00:25:41.478
And company director Kim Ju-won
is her brother.

00:25:41.561 --> 00:25:43.188
Those years as a nerd really help.

00:25:44.397 --> 00:25:47.442
Save it. When you go inside,
you better be on alert.

00:25:47.525 --> 00:25:49.569
You saw how they belittled us.

00:25:51.237 --> 00:25:52.572
Fix your tie too.

00:25:52.655 --> 00:25:54.157
Let's go. Move out.

00:25:54.908 --> 00:25:56.034
Let's go!

00:25:56.117 --> 00:26:01.331
You said earlier we're pro bono attorneys
who defend the weak.

00:26:02.248 --> 00:26:05.001
They don't look that weak at all.

00:26:05.668 --> 00:26:08.546
Since we're here anyway,
we'll explain the situation.

00:26:09.214 --> 00:26:10.590
-Mr. Kim?
-Yes, ma'am.

00:26:14.344 --> 00:26:17.555
I'm going to take videos again today.

00:26:17.639 --> 00:26:19.224
-Yeah.
-She is so pretty.

00:26:19.307 --> 00:26:22.310
Elijah!

00:26:22.894 --> 00:26:24.813
Elijah, can you take off your cap?

00:26:24.896 --> 00:26:25.855
Fuck!

00:26:33.196 --> 00:26:34.030
I'm sorry.

00:26:36.199 --> 00:26:37.742
What's wrong, Elijah?

00:26:37.826 --> 00:26:39.077
Are you okay? Did something--

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:41.746
Enough is enough, you crazy bitches!

00:26:43.456 --> 00:26:44.416
Get lost.

00:26:44.958 --> 00:26:46.918
I said fuck off!

00:26:53.591 --> 00:26:54.968
Were you surprised?

00:26:55.718 --> 00:26:58.221
I'm pretty good at cursing.
And colorfully too.

00:26:58.304 --> 00:26:59.556
Stay still, Elijah.

00:27:00.306 --> 00:27:01.850
Their parents want to sue Elijah,

00:27:01.933 --> 00:27:05.603
claiming their daughters
were hospitalized due to shock.

00:27:05.687 --> 00:27:06.938
If this gets out of hand,

00:27:07.021 --> 00:27:09.315
all her endorsement deals
will be terminated,

00:27:09.399 --> 00:27:11.526
and she'll have to pay
billions of won in penalties.

00:27:11.609 --> 00:27:15.029
Her recent ambassador deal
with a luxury brand will be canceled too.

00:27:15.113 --> 00:27:18.616
There's also an internet channel
that's been harassing her since long ago.

00:27:18.700 --> 00:27:20.410
I told you, everyone.

00:27:20.493 --> 00:27:23.413
This is all plastic surgery and editing.

00:27:23.496 --> 00:27:25.165
Korea's sweetheart, my foot.

00:27:25.707 --> 00:27:30.628
Okay, everyone. Now, I will reveal
Elijah's before photos.

00:27:31.629 --> 00:27:33.173
How much facial contouring did she do?

00:27:33.256 --> 00:27:35.884
With that much surgery,
isn't she more robot than human?

00:27:35.967 --> 00:27:39.888
The whole country is being fooled by her.

00:27:39.971 --> 00:27:44.601
The Cyber Crusader
will uncover the truth on this channel.

00:27:44.684 --> 00:27:47.061
Make sure to turn on notifications,
like, and subscribe!

00:27:47.145 --> 00:27:48.980
My goodness.

00:27:49.606 --> 00:27:52.817
Those are downright lies, of course.

00:27:52.901 --> 00:27:54.944
If they get a hold of this video,

00:27:55.028 --> 00:27:58.448
these lies will turn into the truth.

00:27:58.531 --> 00:27:59.866
The public jumps to conclusions.

00:27:59.949 --> 00:28:01.117
By the way,

00:28:02.452 --> 00:28:04.662
who took this video?

00:28:04.746 --> 00:28:06.831
There must be a camera that recorded it.

00:28:07.624 --> 00:28:09.459
Right. This one?

00:28:09.542 --> 00:28:14.506
Yes, her whole body is in frame,
so it was taken from ten meters away.

00:28:14.589 --> 00:28:15.715
Elijah didn't notice

00:28:16.382 --> 00:28:18.760
that there was a camera at all.

00:28:18.843 --> 00:28:20.720
You think we didn't follow up on it?

00:28:21.346 --> 00:28:23.515
-What?
-The driver of the taxi the girls rented

00:28:23.598 --> 00:28:25.141
took it with the girl's phone.

00:28:26.267 --> 00:28:27.393
They rented a taxi?

00:28:27.477 --> 00:28:30.104
Yes, because it was 3:00 in the morning.

00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:33.483
She gave the phone to the driver
to film them meeting Elijah.

00:28:34.317 --> 00:28:36.861
The video hasn't spread yet?

00:28:36.945 --> 00:28:40.281
Some of the parents
are using the video to ask for money,

00:28:40.865 --> 00:28:42.909
but we've stopped it
from circulating for now.

00:28:42.992 --> 00:28:45.245
Don't worry, Elijah.
I'll make sure nothing gets out.

00:28:45.328 --> 00:28:48.748
Just focus on preparing
for the album, okay?

00:28:58.508 --> 00:29:01.135
Well, the first match was a total defeat.

00:29:01.219 --> 00:29:02.929
They didn't even take our business cards.

00:29:03.012 --> 00:29:06.224
They suddenly called us
when we weren't even ready.

00:29:06.307 --> 00:29:07.141
That was so unfair.

00:29:07.225 --> 00:29:09.477
They don't want us to win at all.

00:29:09.561 --> 00:29:11.896
Are we going to be disbanded
before we even get a chance?

00:29:14.816 --> 00:29:16.943
-What's my name?
-Sorry?

00:29:17.777 --> 00:29:20.238
-What is my name?
-What is he doing?

00:29:23.700 --> 00:29:25.201
Aren't you Mr. Kang Da-wit?

00:29:25.827 --> 00:29:28.997
Yes. It's Da-wit, like David,
who beat the giant Goliath.

00:29:29.080 --> 00:29:32.166
I'm getting tired
of saying it now, okay? We…

00:29:33.001 --> 00:29:35.169
-will win no matter what.
-Yes.

00:29:37.213 --> 00:29:39.966
Sure, sure. As you know,

00:29:40.466 --> 00:29:41.342
I'm always…

00:29:42.176 --> 00:29:43.595
full of faith.

00:29:44.762 --> 00:29:46.055
What's gotten into you?

00:29:46.139 --> 00:29:48.516
But my job is at stake
this time, Mr. Kang.

00:29:49.601 --> 00:29:51.185
Instead of a vague speech,

00:29:51.269 --> 00:29:53.646
you should give us specific measures.

00:29:54.272 --> 00:29:57.108
-Jun-u, why are you so worked up--
-Why wouldn't I be?

00:29:57.859 --> 00:30:00.987
What on earth made you make that bet?

00:30:07.368 --> 00:30:08.661
Mushrooms.

00:30:09.829 --> 00:30:11.205
-Anger issues.
-Hey!

00:30:11.289 --> 00:30:13.875
A serious nerd and a tall idiot.

00:30:13.958 --> 00:30:16.794
How are we going to beat
a mega law firm?

00:30:16.878 --> 00:30:18.004
What's with you?

00:30:18.087 --> 00:30:19.422
-Calm down.
-Let go of me.

00:30:19.505 --> 00:30:20.924
-Sorry, he's drunk.
-I'm not drunk.

00:30:21.007 --> 00:30:22.550
-Sit down.
-I'm not drunk!

00:30:26.804 --> 00:30:27.889
Am I wrong?

00:30:29.307 --> 00:30:31.809
You've done well your entire life,

00:30:31.893 --> 00:30:34.979
so the whole world
is like a joke to you, isn't it?

00:30:35.063 --> 00:30:40.193
This team might be like a hobby for you,
but I tried four times to get this job.

00:30:41.819 --> 00:30:43.404
This job is my lifeline!

00:30:49.577 --> 00:30:51.663
This team is my lifeline too.

00:30:53.331 --> 00:30:54.207
What?

00:30:55.792 --> 00:30:59.379
I was fired after getting blackmailed
with a video of me taking a bribe.

00:31:00.171 --> 00:31:01.714
Then, I came here.

00:31:13.267 --> 00:31:15.061
I've been pushed to the brink too.

00:31:25.279 --> 00:31:26.447
I'm sorry.

00:31:27.156 --> 00:31:28.533
I should have told you before.

00:31:29.450 --> 00:31:30.493
We're on the same team.

00:31:31.327 --> 00:31:33.830
But you knew about it, Gi-ppeum.

00:31:33.913 --> 00:31:35.957
-Well…
-Yeah.

00:31:36.040 --> 00:31:37.125
I'm sorry.

00:31:38.126 --> 00:31:39.460
As I told you,

00:31:40.128 --> 00:31:43.172
I ended up seeing the video very suddenly.

00:31:43.256 --> 00:31:45.466
I couldn't tell you because I wasn't sure.

00:31:45.550 --> 00:31:48.094
Is your judgment
the only one that matters?

00:31:49.262 --> 00:31:51.389
You should have asked for our opinions.

00:31:55.351 --> 00:31:58.521
We ended up working
with a person under suspicion,

00:31:58.604 --> 00:32:01.024
and it was for public interest cases.

00:32:01.816 --> 00:32:02.692
Nan-hui, that's--

00:32:02.775 --> 00:32:05.486
It's not her fault. It's all my fault.

00:32:05.570 --> 00:32:07.780
I should've told you sooner

00:32:07.864 --> 00:32:09.991
and let you decide.

00:32:12.952 --> 00:32:14.662
We'll need to discuss it among ourselves.

00:32:15.913 --> 00:32:17.540
This was very unexpected.

00:32:18.833 --> 00:32:19.792
Right.

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:21.544
Go ahead and discuss.

00:32:27.550 --> 00:32:28.551
I'll step aside.

00:32:37.393 --> 00:32:38.770
Me too?

00:32:41.606 --> 00:32:42.440
Okay.

00:32:43.191 --> 00:32:44.025
All right.

00:32:50.573 --> 00:32:54.160
Geez, why on earth did you bring that up?

00:32:54.243 --> 00:32:55.953
It's either you do or you die.

00:32:56.496 --> 00:32:58.122
We can't win if we can't unite.

00:32:58.206 --> 00:33:00.625
But it's too risky.

00:33:00.708 --> 00:33:03.544
The two of us should've tracked down
the culprit first.

00:33:03.628 --> 00:33:06.547
We needed to check the number
that sent the video to me.

00:33:07.090 --> 00:33:11.219
Ms. Park, I'll handle it
on my own from now on.

00:33:11.302 --> 00:33:14.097
-Don't get involved anymore.
-Mr. Kang.

00:33:14.180 --> 00:33:15.515
It's dangerous.

00:33:15.598 --> 00:33:19.143
The culprit did this to someone
who was a chief judge at the time.

00:33:20.019 --> 00:33:21.771
And he probably didn't do it alone.

00:33:23.397 --> 00:33:25.900
But you are alone.

00:33:26.943 --> 00:33:28.152
You believed me.

00:33:28.903 --> 00:33:29.862
That's enough for me.

00:33:32.031 --> 00:33:33.199
Mr. Kang!

00:33:35.535 --> 00:33:36.619
Okay.

00:33:37.537 --> 00:33:39.413
Let's talk again later.

00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:48.422
The use of sedative makes sense,
but it's still just a theory.

00:33:49.173 --> 00:33:50.424
That's true.

00:33:51.008 --> 00:33:52.510
But we can't be certain

00:33:52.593 --> 00:33:55.388
that Mr. Kang accepted a bribe
based on that one video.

00:33:56.848 --> 00:33:59.767
There are strange circumstances
that Ms. Park found too.

00:34:06.274 --> 00:34:09.527
We've decided to presume
you're innocent until proven guilty.

00:34:10.194 --> 00:34:11.028
Ms. Yoo.

00:34:11.904 --> 00:34:13.698
If what you claim is true,

00:34:14.824 --> 00:34:17.743
it means you're an innocent victim
who was unfairly framed.

00:34:18.953 --> 00:34:21.831
As a pro bono attorney,
I can't ignore such a person.

00:34:25.459 --> 00:34:28.045
-Ms. Yoo.
-Of course, I don't totally trust you.

00:34:28.129 --> 00:34:29.797
Although I've decided to trust you,

00:34:30.590 --> 00:34:33.050
I'll keep my eye on how things go.

00:34:34.302 --> 00:34:35.136
Ms. Yoo.

00:34:37.305 --> 00:34:39.098
I was a bit worked up before.

00:34:39.765 --> 00:34:40.600
I'm sorry.

00:34:41.893 --> 00:34:44.520
But honestly,
I'm very disappointed in you, Mr. Kang.

00:34:45.104 --> 00:34:49.942
You kept saying we were a team,
but you didn't trust us at all.

00:34:54.447 --> 00:34:55.448
I'm sorry.

00:34:56.365 --> 00:34:57.575
I was a coward.

00:34:58.910 --> 00:35:01.370
To be honest, I was afraid

00:35:01.954 --> 00:35:04.957
because I thought
none of you would believe me.

00:35:05.041 --> 00:35:07.335
-Honestly, I didn't really trust you.
-What?

00:35:07.919 --> 00:35:09.587
-Mr. Jang.
-Mr. Jang?

00:35:09.670 --> 00:35:12.506
Every pro bono attorney
has their own reason

00:35:13.257 --> 00:35:14.717
for choosing this job.

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:16.552
But for Mr. Kang,

00:35:17.720 --> 00:35:18.554
I couldn't find his.

00:35:19.347 --> 00:35:22.892
"Why did he force himself
to take a job he didn't want to do?"

00:35:23.809 --> 00:35:26.187
"There must be some other reason

00:35:26.270 --> 00:35:29.523
for using this job as a stepping stone."

00:35:31.192 --> 00:35:35.112
Why didn't you ever ask me
why I took this job?

00:35:35.196 --> 00:35:37.615
Does the intent really matter?

00:35:38.950 --> 00:35:39.951
What?

00:35:40.034 --> 00:35:43.037
You don't need a license
to be a good person and do good things.

00:35:43.663 --> 00:35:45.665
No matter what may be the case,

00:35:46.791 --> 00:35:50.544
you've given it your best
and done well as a pro bono attorney.

00:35:50.628 --> 00:35:53.714
It's okay to wait to see how someone acts
before you criticize them.

00:35:53.798 --> 00:35:57.677
You don't know what their intentions are,
so what's the point of doubting them?

00:36:02.223 --> 00:36:03.391
-Mr. Jang…
-On top of that,

00:36:04.225 --> 00:36:05.476
you're obviously not the type

00:36:06.352 --> 00:36:08.729
to accept a bribe so openly.

00:36:08.813 --> 00:36:10.147
-That's true.
-Yeah.

00:36:10.231 --> 00:36:14.235
He'd cleverly cook up multiple ways
to get away with it before taking one.

00:36:14.318 --> 00:36:16.487
Right? I knew I wasn't
the only one who thought so.

00:36:16.570 --> 00:36:17.655
Yeah.

00:36:19.323 --> 00:36:20.283
What…

00:36:21.450 --> 00:36:24.662
What on earth
did you think of me all this time?

00:36:24.745 --> 00:36:26.122
-A petty--
-Miser.

00:36:26.205 --> 00:36:28.874
-A scrooge.
-An apple box…

00:36:30.418 --> 00:36:32.712
Forget about that.
Treat us to drinks tonight.

00:36:32.795 --> 00:36:35.339
Let have the petty one buy us a drink.

00:36:35.423 --> 00:36:37.758
Okay, tonight's talk ends here.

00:36:37.842 --> 00:36:40.219
When I say "Pro bono,"
you'll say "Let's go."

00:36:40.303 --> 00:36:43.222
-Pro Bono!
-Let's go!

00:36:44.098 --> 00:36:46.726
That didn't really feel…

00:36:46.809 --> 00:36:48.978
Fine. Let's go.

00:36:50.021 --> 00:36:51.731
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

00:37:01.157 --> 00:37:03.868
-I'll go out to the scene of the incident.
-Okay. Good.

00:37:04.660 --> 00:37:06.871
Are you going to check online, Mr. Jang?

00:37:09.957 --> 00:37:11.459
Mr. Kang.

00:37:11.542 --> 00:37:13.169
-Yes?
-What are you looking at?

00:37:13.252 --> 00:37:14.420
Well…

00:37:15.963 --> 00:37:17.631
What are you doing? You're in the way.

00:37:22.136 --> 00:37:23.179
What?

00:37:23.262 --> 00:37:24.555
Why are you all so free?

00:37:24.638 --> 00:37:26.390
-What brings you here?
-What do you think?

00:37:26.474 --> 00:37:29.101
-You got crushed at the first meeting?
-Geez.

00:37:29.977 --> 00:37:30.978
It wasn't that bad.

00:37:31.062 --> 00:37:33.356
I barely appeased Ms. Cha
and got a second meeting.

00:37:34.231 --> 00:37:35.858
It's at EK Entertainment this time.

00:37:35.941 --> 00:37:38.027
You'll pitch against Baekseung.

00:37:38.694 --> 00:37:40.654
What? A pitch?

00:37:41.530 --> 00:37:42.823
Come with me, everyone.

00:37:42.907 --> 00:37:44.533
Now? Where to all of a sudden?

00:37:45.076 --> 00:37:46.285
To get ready for battle.

00:37:51.832 --> 00:37:52.833
I'll get going.

00:37:56.212 --> 00:37:57.380
They look so expensive.

00:38:04.136 --> 00:38:06.555
This kind of outfit
actually suits you, Ms. Park.

00:38:06.639 --> 00:38:08.349
But Ms. Oh,

00:38:08.432 --> 00:38:10.351
the price isn't written here.

00:38:10.434 --> 00:38:11.894
Don't worry about that.

00:38:12.520 --> 00:38:14.730
How could I not worry?
You know how much my salary is.

00:38:14.814 --> 00:38:18.984
Just win. If you lose,
that will be your severance pay.

00:38:19.527 --> 00:38:20.945
Oh, my gosh. It's that expensive?

00:38:25.783 --> 00:38:26.909
Ms. Park.

00:38:26.992 --> 00:38:27.910
-How do I look?
-Move.

00:38:33.499 --> 00:38:34.583
This is a nice color.

00:38:34.667 --> 00:38:36.836
Are you going to bring
all your team members?

00:38:38.504 --> 00:38:41.507
-What?
-The client's fussy about qualifications.

00:38:41.590 --> 00:38:43.426
How about going
with just Ms. Park this time?

00:38:46.262 --> 00:38:48.180
They're my team.
They each have their own role.

00:38:48.848 --> 00:38:49.682
Is that so?

00:38:50.349 --> 00:38:51.392
Gosh, this…

00:38:51.475 --> 00:38:52.643
-What?
-This looks cool.

00:38:52.726 --> 00:38:54.103
How's this? How do I look?

00:38:54.186 --> 00:38:56.522
-Is this over your card limit?
-No way.

00:38:57.064 --> 00:38:59.275
Excuse me. Please pay for all of them.

00:38:59.358 --> 00:39:00.317
Yes, ma'am.

00:39:01.068 --> 00:39:02.820
The CEO's company card.

00:39:03.696 --> 00:39:05.448
-Hold on.
-Yes?

00:39:08.617 --> 00:39:11.328
Thank you for the other day with Dad.

00:39:13.122 --> 00:39:14.123
Don't mention it.

00:39:16.792 --> 00:39:17.793
Good luck.

00:39:18.752 --> 00:39:19.962
Don't embarrass me.

00:39:27.511 --> 00:39:29.138
So, what's your solution?

00:39:29.221 --> 00:39:30.514
We believe

00:39:30.598 --> 00:39:33.309
the best option is to fix things
as quickly as possible.

00:39:34.059 --> 00:39:37.730
We'll meet with the girls' parents,
pay them an adequate settlement,

00:39:37.813 --> 00:39:41.108
and get them to sign an NDA
and an agreement

00:39:41.192 --> 00:39:43.611
to not file any civil
or criminal lawsuits.

00:39:43.694 --> 00:39:46.697
"The signatory will not file
any civil or criminal lawsuits

00:39:46.780 --> 00:39:48.282
on this matter in the future."

00:39:48.866 --> 00:39:49.700
It's neat and clean.

00:39:50.493 --> 00:39:54.580
But aren't we giving
too much money for the settlement?

00:39:55.623 --> 00:39:58.334
Why do we have to pay them so much
for a broken camera?

00:39:58.417 --> 00:40:02.087
You have to consider
the cost of Elijah's public image.

00:40:02.171 --> 00:40:03.255
That's right, Ju-won.

00:40:03.797 --> 00:40:06.091
It's about your sister.
We shouldn't save our pennies.

00:40:06.175 --> 00:40:07.676
Still…

00:40:07.760 --> 00:40:10.179
Oh & Partners are a bit late.

00:40:28.864 --> 00:40:31.992
Why are they walking
in a flying V formation?

00:40:34.203 --> 00:40:35.329
What on earth?

00:40:47.716 --> 00:40:49.218
Are they the same team?

00:40:55.558 --> 00:40:56.809
Where are they?

00:40:56.892 --> 00:40:57.726
I see them.

00:40:58.352 --> 00:40:59.353
Me too.

00:41:01.855 --> 00:41:04.441
Sorry, we're late. We're Team Pro Bono.

00:41:05.693 --> 00:41:07.027
You're the same team from before?

00:41:07.653 --> 00:41:09.697
Yes. We are, Elijah.

00:41:10.281 --> 00:41:12.533
Were you on a makeover show or something?

00:41:13.409 --> 00:41:15.119
For an attorney,

00:41:16.120 --> 00:41:18.122
a suit is like armor.

00:41:18.747 --> 00:41:19.582
Cool.

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:24.378
From now on,
we'll be protecting you, Elijah.

00:41:25.421 --> 00:41:26.255
Just be on time.

00:41:28.966 --> 00:41:33.095
I guess you were stunned
after I beat you. What was that?

00:41:33.596 --> 00:41:35.097
A suit of armor?

00:41:35.180 --> 00:41:37.141
Do you know each other? Same university?

00:41:39.351 --> 00:41:41.729
He's a legendary figure.

00:41:41.812 --> 00:41:44.231
He was appointed to court
with only a high school degree.

00:41:44.315 --> 00:41:46.483
How amazing is that?

00:41:47.735 --> 00:41:48.736
You must be kidding.

00:41:51.614 --> 00:41:54.700
No, he's right.
I only have a high school diploma.

00:41:54.783 --> 00:41:57.202
I knew you didn't go to SNU, but…

00:41:58.871 --> 00:42:02.041
If the team leader didn't go to college,
what about the others?

00:42:02.124 --> 00:42:04.752
Ms. Park Gi-ppeum graduated
from SNU Law School.

00:42:04.835 --> 00:42:06.629
And what about you?

00:42:07.963 --> 00:42:10.257
Well, I…

00:42:10.341 --> 00:42:13.135
You might not be familiar with it.

00:42:13.218 --> 00:42:14.053
It's far down…

00:42:14.845 --> 00:42:15.721
in the south.

00:42:17.056 --> 00:42:19.725
In the south. Isn't that amazing?

00:42:19.808 --> 00:42:23.062
They ignore academic and work backgrounds.

00:42:24.980 --> 00:42:28.567
Do you litigate with your college diploma?

00:42:28.651 --> 00:42:30.319
Not at all.

00:42:30.402 --> 00:42:32.946
I go in fully prepared.

00:42:33.030 --> 00:42:34.281
I see.

00:42:34.365 --> 00:42:36.867
We have warned the parents already.

00:42:36.950 --> 00:42:40.412
"If the video leaks, you'll face a lawsuit

00:42:40.496 --> 00:42:44.583
demanding a devastating amount of money
from Baekseung Law Firm."

00:42:44.667 --> 00:42:45.709
So don't worry about it.

00:42:46.960 --> 00:42:49.630
You're way too confident about this.

00:42:50.464 --> 00:42:52.800
-What?
-That kind of video

00:42:52.883 --> 00:42:55.260
is like a knife that could stab someone.

00:42:55.886 --> 00:42:58.305
No matter what, once the knife is made,

00:42:58.389 --> 00:43:00.724
it'll end up stabbing someone.

00:43:02.184 --> 00:43:03.268
Did something happen?

00:43:04.812 --> 00:43:07.147
To prepare contingency plans,

00:43:07.231 --> 00:43:08.816
our team has been monitoring

00:43:08.899 --> 00:43:11.110
the changes in traffic of her fansite

00:43:11.193 --> 00:43:12.945
and related pages in real time.

00:43:13.612 --> 00:43:16.907
Mr. Jang here once made an app
for such things.

00:43:17.908 --> 00:43:21.120
I just checked traffic on my way here,

00:43:21.787 --> 00:43:23.330
and on Cyber Crusader's channel,

00:43:23.914 --> 00:43:25.666
this video was uploaded.

00:43:26.667 --> 00:43:27.751
What?

00:43:29.336 --> 00:43:32.256
Hey, didn't you say
you took care of the parents?

00:43:32.339 --> 00:43:35.092
I did, and I sufficiently warned them.
The situation--

00:43:35.175 --> 00:43:38.220
Did you check the taxi driver's phone too?

00:43:38.303 --> 00:43:41.056
He shot it with the phone
one of the girls gave him.

00:43:41.140 --> 00:43:42.182
Don't you get it?

00:43:42.725 --> 00:43:46.520
The taxi driver took it
with his own phone and sent it.

00:43:48.397 --> 00:43:52.693
In K-pop idol fandom, there's something
called an "ST." You know that, right?

00:43:56.947 --> 00:43:58.115
An ST?

00:43:59.032 --> 00:44:01.076
It's short for "stalker taxi."

00:44:01.702 --> 00:44:04.580
These sasaeng fans, or obsessive fans,

00:44:04.663 --> 00:44:07.291
use these taxis to stalk celebrities.

00:44:07.374 --> 00:44:10.794
It means he wasn't just
a regular taxi driver.

00:44:10.878 --> 00:44:14.423
Do you think someone like that
would stay quiet after shooting a video

00:44:14.506 --> 00:44:16.133
that will make him a fortune?

00:44:17.551 --> 00:44:22.264
I guess not enough research
was done on the client's industry.

00:44:24.308 --> 00:44:26.518
Ms. Cha, you don't have to worry.

00:44:26.602 --> 00:44:28.020
We can handle this.

00:44:28.103 --> 00:44:29.021
How?

00:44:29.104 --> 00:44:30.981
They said it's already been uploaded!

00:44:31.064 --> 00:44:34.443
We'll send a certified letter
in our firm's name to the channel owner.

00:44:34.526 --> 00:44:36.653
"Take it down immediately,
or you'll be held liable."

00:44:36.737 --> 00:44:38.989
"Take the video down,
and let's meet to settle."

00:44:39.573 --> 00:44:40.783
I'll make sure to resolve it.

00:44:40.866 --> 00:44:44.119
It's probably spread
all over the place by now!

00:44:44.203 --> 00:44:46.747
You should admit your daughter
to a hospital for now.

00:44:46.830 --> 00:44:47.664
What?

00:44:48.290 --> 00:44:51.251
"Due to severe insomnia and anxiety
caused by exhaustion from her tour

00:44:51.335 --> 00:44:54.630
and her new album preparation,
she wasn't thinking straight."

00:44:55.297 --> 00:44:57.549
"Her doctors ordered her to rest,
so she was admitted."

00:44:57.633 --> 00:45:00.302
"But there is no excuse
for committing a huge mistake

00:45:00.385 --> 00:45:02.679
of treating her fans like this."

00:45:02.763 --> 00:45:06.558
"She deeply apologizes to everyone
who are disappointed."

00:45:06.642 --> 00:45:07.476
And then,

00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:11.813
she needs to cry cutely
at the right moment.

00:45:14.733 --> 00:45:17.110
You want me to "cry cutely"?

00:45:20.989 --> 00:45:23.200
My choice of words was a bit poor.
I apologize.

00:45:23.283 --> 00:45:26.495
The important thing is
we need to keep emotions out of this

00:45:26.578 --> 00:45:29.122
and give the public what they want

00:45:29.206 --> 00:45:30.958
as quickly as possible.

00:45:31.625 --> 00:45:35.420
Isn't it important
to set all the facts straight first?

00:45:36.505 --> 00:45:39.174
What do you mean?

00:45:39.258 --> 00:45:40.467
To see if anything was missed,

00:45:40.551 --> 00:45:42.636
I went to the security office
of her apartment.

00:45:42.719 --> 00:45:44.596
I watched
the surveillance footage all night.

00:45:45.180 --> 00:45:47.808
It wasn't the girls' first time there.

00:45:51.353 --> 00:45:52.813
Hey, when is she coming out?

00:45:52.896 --> 00:45:56.066
-Elijah!
-Elijah!

00:45:56.149 --> 00:45:57.818
Come on. It's not her.

00:45:57.901 --> 00:45:59.444
-Shut up, bitch.
-Are you blind?

00:45:59.528 --> 00:46:00.696
You're here again?

00:46:00.779 --> 00:46:04.408
I warned you I'd call the cops next time.

00:46:04.491 --> 00:46:06.535
You'll call the cops on us?

00:46:06.618 --> 00:46:08.245
What? Who are you to say that, old lady?

00:46:08.328 --> 00:46:10.497
Hey, she's the stylist
who stopped us before.

00:46:10.581 --> 00:46:14.376
Right. I remember that fucking ugly face.

00:46:14.459 --> 00:46:17.087
A mere stylist calling the cops on us?
What the hell?

